a simple technique for digital division.wa simple and economical method for digitaldivision is described.  the method is suitable for divisors whose leading character is either radix lessone or is unity with the next character equal to zero; also the method is direct and needs only half thenumber of arithmetic operations needed by a variant of the harvard iterative method, described by gilman,which is suitable for similar divisors.cacm june, nandi, s. k.krishnamurthy, e. v.ca jb february ,   : am